<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1441,1826]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">
This taxon has not been recorded since the 1950s and 
<bibRefCitation author="Tamanini" box="[806,993,1693,1718]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" refString="Tamanini, L. (1979) Eterotteri acquatici (Heteroptera: Gerromorpha, Nepomorpha). Consiglio Nazionale delle Ricerche, Verona, 106 pp." type="book" year="1979">Tamanini (1979)</bibRefCitation>
expressed his doubts about the validity of the species, which may be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[645,789,1730,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis box="[645,789,1730,1753]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">H. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName box="[827,1043,1729,1754]" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" genus="Lygaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="pusillus" subSpecies="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[827,1043,1729,1754]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">H. pusillus pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Theoretically, 
<taxonomicName box="[1220,1401,1729,1754]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericeus">
<emphasis box="[1220,1401,1729,1754]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">Hebrus sericeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Costa" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" refString="Costa, A. (1864) Peregrinazione zoologica. Annuario del Museo Zoologico della R. Universita di Napoli, 2, 119 - 125." type="journal article" year="1864">
<collectingRegion box="[1409,1432,1730,1754]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">A</collectingRegion>
. 
<collectingRegion box="[151,218,1766,1790]" country="Tanzania" name="Pwani" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">Costa</collectingRegion>
, 1864
</bibRefCitation>
, described from environs of Benevento in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[897,949,1765,1790]" name="Italy" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">Italy</collectingCountry>
and considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" genus="Lygaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="pusillus" subSpecies="pusillus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">H. pusillus pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, may be the senior synonym of this taxon. This taxon is in urgent need of revision.
</paragraph>
